

Podcast at http://www.againstthegrain.org/AtG%202007.09.18_Eco-localism.mp3


=Description=

"If your goal is ecological sustainability, how often have you been urged to get active on the local level? Greg Albo critiques localist projects that deny or ignore the extra-local capitalist and neoliberal context. He also questions whether small-scale enterprises and local political practice are in fact more environmentally responsible and democratic."
(http://www.socialistproject.ca/environment/)


